1.0.0 ¬∑ [source](https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.80.0/src/alloc/ffi/c_str.rs.html#264)

Creates a new C-compatible string from a container of bytes.

This function will consume the provided data and use the underlying bytes to construct a new string, ensuring that there is a trailing 0 byte. This trailing 0 byte will be appended by this function; the provided data should _not_ contain any 0 bytes in it.

##### [¬ß](#examples-1)Examples

[‚ìò](# "This example is not tested")

```
use std::ffi::CString;
use std::os::raw::c_char;

extern "C" { fn puts(s: *const c_char); }

let to_print = CString::new("Hello!").expect("CString::new failed");
unsafe {
    puts(to_print.as_ptr());
}
```

