Converts a `[Vec](../../vec/struct.Vec.html "struct std::vec::Vec")<[u8](../../primitive.u8.html "primitive u8")>` to a [`CString`](../struct.CString.html "struct std::ffi::CString") without checking the invariants on the given [`Vec`](../../vec/struct.Vec.html "struct std::vec::Vec").

##### [¬ß](#safety-2)Safety

The given [`Vec`](../../vec/struct.Vec.html "struct std::vec::Vec") **must** have one nul byte as its last element. This means it cannot be empty nor have any other nul byte anywhere else.

##### [¬ß](#example)Example

```
use std::ffi::CString;
assert_eq!(
    unsafe { CString::from_vec_with_nul_unchecked(b"abc\0".to_vec()) },
    unsafe { CString::from_vec_unchecked(b"abc".to_vec()) }
);
```

